---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy – DuoTake";
---

<Layout
    title={title}
    favicon="apps/duotake/favicon.png"
    description="Privacy policy for DuoTake."
    robots="noindex, follow"
>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h1>{title}</h1>

            <h4>Last updated: 16/04/2026</h4>

            <p>
                DuoTake respects your privacy and is committed to being clear about how
                your information is handled when you use the app.
            </p>

            <h3>1. Personal Data Collection</h3>

            <p>
                DuoTake is designed to capture photos and videos directly on your device.
                We do not require account creation and we do not collect personal data
                such as your name, email address, phone number, or location for our own
                servers.
            </p>

            <h3>2. Camera, Microphone, and Photo Library Access</h3>

            <p>
                DuoTake may request access to your device camera, microphone, and photo
                library only so the app can record media and save your files.
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Camera:</strong> used to capture photos and videos.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Microphone:</strong> used when recording video with audio.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Photo Library:</strong> used to save captures or access media
                    you choose to manage through the app.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                This access is limited to the functionality of the app and is controlled
                by iOS permissions on your device.
            </p>

            <h3>3. On-Device Processing</h3>

            <p>
                DuoTake processes captured media locally on your device so it can produce
                portrait and landscape outputs from the same session. We do not upload
                your photos, videos, or audio recordings to servers controlled by the
                developer.
            </p>

            <h3>4. Purchases</h3>

            <p>
                If you purchase premium features, the transaction is processed by Apple
                through the App Store. We do not receive your full payment details such as
                credit card information. Purchase status and restoration are handled using
                Apple services.
            </p>

            <h3>5. Data Sharing</h3>

            <p>
                We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for
                advertising or marketing purposes.
            </p>

            <h3>6. Data Retention</h3>

            <p>
                Because DuoTake is designed to work without developer-hosted user
                accounts, we do not maintain a remote database of your personal media.
                Files created with the app remain under your control on your device and
                in services you choose to use, such as Apple Photos or iCloud.
            </p>

            <h3>7. Security</h3>

            <p>
                Although DuoTake does not store your media on developer servers, we still
                aim to follow good security practices in the app and minimize unnecessary
                access to device information.
            </p>

            <h3>8. Children’s Privacy</h3>

            <p>
                DuoTake is not intended to knowingly collect personal information from
                children. If you believe the app has collected information in a way that
                conflicts with this policy, please contact us.
            </p>

            <h3>9. Changes to This Policy</h3>

            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in
                app functionality, legal requirements, or how DuoTake operates. The latest
                version will always be available on this page.
            </p>

            <h3>10. Contact</h3>

            <p>
                If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or DuoTake, please
                contact us at:
                <a href="mailto:adrianosouzacostaios@gmail.com">adrianosouzacostaios@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    main {
        padding: calc(64px + var(--safe-area-top)) var(--safe-page-padding-right) calc(64px + var(--safe-area-bottom)) var(--safe-page-padding-left);
        max-width: 780px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    p {
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    h1 { margin-bottom: 32px; }
    h3, h4 { margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    ul { padding-left: 20px; list-style: disc; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    li { margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    a { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
